<br>
We have already strong tools to manipulate the outer world`s condition. The real question is that in such way we manipulate our own human condition. <br>
<br>
In natural terms our extremelly long survival as species, or thread of species, or chaotic evolutionary tree structure of post-humanities is inevitable. For that purpose, we don`t have to tame the whole galaxy or the local group in vast boring uniformity of Suns and Earths, diyng slower. Multuple alternatives are plausible. If we survive as we are or close to the nowaday human condition, our progeny could chose to justb observe the natural processes and simply to avoid the immediate calamities, the same way we (want to) live here on Earth in 'ecological' manner... At least some of our descendants...<br>
<br>
BTW, personally I like the picture of interstellar or even intergalasctic nomadness, filling the universe as a gas of humans dressed in common biospheres` bubles. This 'gas' will be the same for the vast voids as the monocellular life for the earts biosphere - bacteria, viruses, mono-fungi... But together with the bacterias shall be also other - trees, himans, rabits, crocodiles and gods...<br>
